CHANGES0009: Extract EvenOdd library + refactor LLPO to use it

New file: EvenOdd.agda (391 lines)
- Self-contained even/odd library with multiple interfaces:
  - Parity data type (even k / odd k constructors)
  - Sigma witnesses: Even n, Odd n (using double), Even+ n, Odd+ n, Odd+' n (using +)
  - Bool-valued: isEven/isOdd with full conversion suite
- Core functions: double, half, with round-trip lemmas
- Conversions between all interfaces
- Decidability (even-or-odd), mutual exclusion (not-Even-and-Odd)
- Parity of addition (Even+Even→Even, etc.)
- Convenience eliminators (parityElim, parityRec, evenOddElim)

Refactored: LLPO.agda (1330 → 1270 lines, -60 lines)
- Removed inline even/odd definitions (double, half, isEven-double, etc.)
- Removed inline even→eq, odd→eq proofs
- Added import of LLPOwork.EvenOdd with renaming for backward compatibility:
  isEven-suc-double → isOdd-double+1, double-half-even → double-half,
  suc-double-half-odd → suc-double-half, half-suc-double → half-double+1
- All existing code unchanged; only the import source changed
- Both files compile successfully, zero postulates, zero holes

The 60-line decrease in LLPO.agda is accounted for by the extracted definitions
now living in EvenOdd.agda (which contains those plus many additional results).
No useful work was removed.
